{"by":"sminchev","id":47777299,"kids":[47777481,47778770,47778169,47778614,47778952,47777320,47777963],"parent":47776557,"text":"How can I explain to my 6 months old girl that we all need to sleep :D<p>This is a bug in the universe! We need to sleep so that the levels of dopamine, and hormones of hunger and not hunger are at good levels, so that we can be healthy and strong, so that the immune system is stable and strong... And we need to get good sleep so that we can protect our children and be sane....<p>BUT the nature decided that the kids will wake up 3-4 times per night, and you need to wake up and take care of them.<p>You sleep in best case, on pauses, not more than 4-6 hours, you feel miserable, and at the same time you are THE HAPPIEST PERSON IN THIS WORLD! :)","time":1776250324,"type":"comment"}